messages.messageBody:
Holly's composite photo is great! My 13-year-old daughter is becoming
very interested in photography. We have a good Nikon, and we do not
have a digital camera, but we need one. Dd's photographic spurts
require immediate results, which means she's been using disposable
cameras with one-hour processing from CVS.

Any tips on where to get a used digital camera, other than e-Bay,
which we are persuing, would be appreciated. You can email me off-list.
Thanks,
Susan
Again, great picture, Holly!

messages.messageBody:
http://sandradodd.blogspot.com/

This is exciting to me. We have a cheapish Adobe Photoshop subset of
stuff called Photoshop Elements 2.0
There are probably newer versions of that. I think I paid $90 when
it was barely obsolete. But Holly and Marty have learned to do some
very cool things with it.

Sandra
